1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,920
React can render lists from arrays, you need JavaScript's map method, that's it.

2
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:14,960
Call array.map, pass a function, return JSX, react renders one element per item.

3
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:17,440
Each list item needs a key prop.

4
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:22,520
Keys help React track which items changed, were added or removed.

5
00:00:22,520 --> 00:00:27,680
Keys must be unique among siblings, they don't need to be globally unique, just within

6
00:00:27,680 --> 00:00:28,960
that list.

7
00:00:28,960 --> 00:00:34,640
You stable ID from your data as keys, database ID are ideal.

8
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:40,000
Don't use array indexes as keys unless the list never changes order.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,840
Index keys break when items move.

10
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:45,560
Never use math.random as a key.

11
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:49,440
It changes every render and destroys performance.

12
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,600
Keys are not passed as props.

13
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:57,080
If your component needs the ID, pass it as a separate prop with a different name.

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,480
You can filter and map together.

15
00:00:59,480 --> 00:01:03,720
Call array.filter first, then dot map on the results.

16
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:11,160
JSX lets you embed the whole map expression inside curly braces, right in the return statement.

17
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:16,920
If your list items need more than one DOM element, wrap them in a fragment.

18
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:21,480
Fragments let you add a key without adding extra DOM nodes.

19
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:23,680
Nested lists work the same way.

20
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:26,880
Map inside map, each with its own key.

21
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:30,400
Act shows a warning in the console if keys are missing.

22
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:35,480
Take it seriously, it means list updates will be slow or incorrect.

23
00:01:35,480 --> 00:01:41,560
Let's recap, use map to render lists, give every item a stable key, avoid indexes and

24
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,360
random values.

25
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,360
Next up, keeping components pure.

